(136, 'chalazion cured by  EASY, SAFE, FAST & COST EFFECTIVE TREATMENT', 'chalazion cured by  EASY, SAFE, FAST & COST EFFECTIVE TREATMENT ..\nChalazion is a cyst in the eyelid due to a blocked oil gland.[4] They are typically in the middle of the eyelid, red, and non painful. They tend to come on gradually over a few weeks.[2]\n\nA chalazion may occur following a stye or from hardened oils blocking the gland.[2] The blocked gland is usually the meibomian gland but can also be the gland of Zeis.[5] A stye and cellulitis may appear similar. A stye, however, is usually more sudden in onset, painful, and occurs at the edge of the eyelid. Cellulitis is also typically painful.[2]\n\nTreatment is typically initially with warm compresses. If this is not effective injecting steroids into the lesion may be tried. If large, incision and drainage may be recommended.[2] While relatively common the frequency of the condition is unknown.[3] The term is from the Greek \"khalazion\" meaning \"small hailstone\".[6]\nDR ARPIT CHOPRA (MD HOMOEOPATHY)\nChief Consultant Homoeopath & Biochemic\nAAROGYA SUPERSPECIALITY MODERN HOMOEOPATHIC CLINIC(Computerised)\n102, First Floor, Krishna Tower, Opposite Curewell\nHospital, Newpalasia, Indore (M.P.)\nMob 9713092737 /  9713037737/ 9907527914(whats up no)\nPH - 0731-2532737, 3961737\nwebsite- www.homoeopathycure.com', 1, 'https://atzean.com/arogya-wp/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/159.webp', '', '2023-01-30 12:20:01', '2023-01-30 12:20:01', 'chalazion cured by  EASY, SAFE, FAST & COST EFFECTIVE TREATMENT', '', '', '', ''),
